<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id904166a2-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s3656"><num value="3656">§ 3656.</num><heading> Uniform application of standards and rates</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The standards established pursuant to <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s3653">section 3653 of this title</ref> and the rates of basic pay established pursuant to <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s3642">section 3642 of this title</ref> shall be applied without regard to whether the employee or individual concerned is a citizen of the United States or a citizen of the Republic of Panama.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id904166a3-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/70/tI/s1216">Pub. L. 96–70, title I, § 1216</ref>, <date date="1979-09-27">Sept. 27, 1979</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/93/465">93 Stat. 465</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/105/85/dC/tXXXV/s3523/c/1">Pub. L. 105–85, div. C, title XXXV, § 3523(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="1997-11-18">Nov. 18, 1997</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/111/2065">111 Stat. 2065</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id904166a4-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
